{
  "answer": "**The *Kātyāyana Smṛti* (work slug: `unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2`), Chapter 72, declares the category of impartible wealth called *dhvajāhṛta* — literally 'what is won under the banner' — and defines it as follows:**\n\n> What is won under the banner (*dhvajāhṛta*) is remembered as not to be divided. What is brought from battle after routing the enemy's army, having risked one's life for the master, is called won under the banner. // K_878 //[^1]\n\n[^1]: *Kātyāyana Smṛti*, [Chapter 72, paragraph p-89ec8b](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/72/translation/#p-89ec8b/).",
